best weekend. to the moon and back.

Things that have been great about driving lately:
Open windows, crisp breeze
Taking shoes off after class and driving barefoot (note: crisp breeze)
Beautiful bright bright bright autumn leaves everywhere, enough to make your heart explode
Blasting tunes, and singing until my voice cracks
Greeting the deer and the squirrels walking alongside the road very enthusiastically
Laughing at myself alone in my car (see above two)
I want to go to the Carlyle and listen to jazz all night
reina has this candle shaped as a white kitten that we just lit. the wax is dripping down one of its eyes and looks like its crying. its the saddest site.

dear friends, 
im in a pickle. i had the hard drive to my computer replaced and lost all my music. but hey no problem because all my music is on my ipod right? WRONG! my ipod is busted now, too! and i'm afraid it's past the point of repair. ive been without my music for weeks now and i feel like im dying slowly. its a major bummer on top of other things. 
what would make me reeeallly really happy would be either mix cds, or even just some friendly file sharing online. i would appreciate it more than anything!

loooove, 
aly

wow life is really good to me lately.. in that not at all kind of sense. 

and i just spilled a full cup of hot coffee all over myself and chemistry books. nice.
can't sleep. i miss a lot of things

i miss having peanut butter and jelly sandwiches and tea at 4 in the morning with andrew at school while we were supposed to be studying for a test the next day or just staying awake doing nothing at all except enjoying eachothers company

i remember one day several years back i went for a walk and sat in the grass and decided that i would figure everything out: the things in my life that confused me, where i was headed, who i was.. and not a single thought came to mind. i didn't figure out anything. everything always unfolds itself.

so freshman year of college is done! i never really updated while i was there and didnt take many photos since i just got a camera recently but.. to generalize, a lot of the following happened: my room very beginning of the year when i had a bunk bed and two roommates. thats jen, the roomie that stayed roomie that moved out, caroline roomie jen reina and me in the nature preserve sup binghamton reina, pat, and me at one of jill's parties lol andrew in my room so many naps here reina and me.. losing our minds haha.. pat, jon and me sister et moi hah halloweeeen being an emt winning awards for harpur's ferry our chiefs boys haha andrew being creepy THE BEAR aka.. andrews roommate beard more great naps here.. old times.. my graduate fam! .... haha love you guyzzz and megan and charo duh so yeah, i guess this is kind of a wrap up, a lot of great things happened, i had a lot of fun, next year is going to be weirdly differently though but im still excited for it

i had a dream that i was house sitting while my aunt was away on vacation. somehow i came across a venus fly trap-esque plant like in Little Shop of Horrors, so i guess i was kind of like seymour and the plant needed to eat and was begging me to feed it. but then the plant went into the fridge and ate my aunt's leftover manicotti. 
when i woke up in the morning i thought this was the funniest thing ever. MAN-icotti. get it. 
hmph

i am shocked and devastated. my mom called and woke me up this morning to tell me what happened. i couldn't believe it. he was one of my idols and i've always had the hopeful intentions of meeting him someday. he completely revolutionized environmental education and has done so much to conserve wildlife. i don't know what to think right now, it was such a freak accident. i'm so upset.
